{"ts":"2026-06-27T04:08:24.666Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Analyzing Component Structure**\n\nI'm currently dissecting the structure of the client/portal/projects page, focusing on its mock data implementation. I'm exploring the feasibility of constructing highly reusable `DataTable` and detail drawer components, seeking to improve efficiency and maintainability, for use across multiple areas of the application.\n\n\n**Refining Component Specifications**\n\nI'm now zeroing in on the specifications, including handling the various dataset types. Reviewing the task, I see the requirement for reusable table, list, filter, and detail-drawer components for both portal and admin pages (excluding the landing page). The components should support search, filtering, sorting, empty states, row clicks, mobile card fallback, and keyboard navigation. I'm exploring the initial implementation.\n\n\n**Designing Interactive Table**\n\nI've decided to tackle `components/private-app/data-tables.tsx` by rewriting it. I'm focusing on creating a premium, interactive `DataTable` and detail drawer. The design will be a \"Sovereign Telemetry Terminal\" experience, aiming for a secure, responsive, and quantum-grade feel. I'm starting with an internal design plan, outlining the page narrative and visual metaphor to guide the component's development.\n\n\n**Visualizing Interface Details**\n\nI'm now deeply immersed in the visual and interactive aspects, envisioning an enterprise flight instrument panel aesthetic. I'm focusing on features such as subtle active pings for each row, monospaced ID badges, and cyber-industrial details. A dynamic side drawer overlay, the \"Enclave Drawer\", will show real-time system logs. I'm also considering the layout strategy, with search, status, and type filters, a sticky header table with custom borders and spacious cells, and a mobile fallback to card items with status badges.\n\n\n**Defining Component Interactions**\n\nI'm now outlining micro-interactions, like copy-to-clipboard with a success state and interactive status lights, for the list and detail drawer. I'm also planning the mobile strategy, considering flexbox-based mobile card rendering, accessible touch areas, and full-screen/slide-up sheet drawer for details. I'll rewrite `components/private-app/data-tables.tsx` into a reusable, premium component, but avoid the landing page files. I am reviewing the current contents of `components/private-app/data-tables.tsx`. I am going to make sure to meet all the requirements like filtering, searching and accessible keyboard navigation.\n\n\n**Integrating Detail Drawer**\n\nI'm now integrating the detail drawer design with the DataTable, exploring inlining or standalone options. The `TableColumn` type will be supported. I'm focusing on lines 7-35 of `components/private-app/data-tables.tsx` to understand existing props. I need to make sure to design a robust component that works for various API contracts.\n\n\n**Developing Detail Drawer**\n\nI'm now implementing the slide-in detail drawer, aiming for a premium experience. I plan to include a real-time cryptographic log feed for a high-end feel, and am focusing on the visual elements. The drawer will slide in from the right, with a dynamic header, cryptographic details, and a simulated ledger signature. A simulated terminal will stream enclave checks, with a close button to complete the UI.\n\n\n**Defining Keyboard Accessibility**\n\nI'm now focusing on full keyboard accessibility for the DataTable, considering focus trapping, keyboard-triggered detail opens, and `aria-dialog` features. I'm exploring the `statusOptions` and `typeOptions` to determine if we can build a combined top control panel for search and filtering within the table. I'm also ensuring the correct imports from `lucide-react`, like `Search, X, ArrowUpDown, Terminal, Shield, Lock, Activity, Copy, Check, ChevronRight, ChevronLeft, SlidersHorizontal, ArrowUpRight` and handling empty states using `<EmptyState />`. I'm starting the drafting of the DataTable implementation, considering the generic type.\n\n\n"}}
